    <thetext>Description of problem:

In the past two days I&apos;ve seen the same behaviour on two different architectures (i686 and armv7hl):  a group install fails for what ever reason, resulting in the group not being fulling installed, yet the group is marked as installed.

In the most recent case, there were 147 missing packages.  These were then manually installed successfully.

How reproducible:

Seems very reproducible ... if the group install fails.

Steps to Reproduce:

1.  Do a fresh install.
2.  Try to install a group, which fails.
3.  Retry to install the same group.
5.  Retry fails as group is reported as already installed.

Actual results:

Group is not actually installed.

Expected results:

Group should be installed.

Additional info:

Both times the group install failed after a fresh system install.  The group being installed was &quot;MATE Desktop&quot; on i686 and &quot;Xfce Desktop&quot; on armv7hl, which only the large-ish number of packages in the group seems relevant (more likely to cause some sort of dependency error on the first group install).</thetext>
